Program: Outlook
Title: Chris Patten talks about Hong Kong
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p03kbs9w
Last Broadcast Date: Not available
An interview with Chris Patten, the last British governor of Hong Kong. Also, Kashmir's first women's magazine. Firefighter Paul Dadge recalls how the 7/7 July bombings changed his life. A victim of the 1984 famine in Ethiopia talks about life there now. Advice for American tourists travelling abroad. Show less